      "sc:citation": {
        "@id": "https://doi.org/10.1101/2023.04.23.536620"
      },
      "sc:description": "HERON is a software package for analyzing peptide binding array data. In addition to identifying significant binding probes, HERON also provides functions for finding epitopes (string of consecutive peptides within a protein). HERON also calculates significance on the probe, epitope, and protein level by employing meta p-value methods.  HERON is designed for obtaining calls on the sample level and calculates fractions of hits for different conditions.",
